data.enText: if sth overturns , or if sb overturns it, it turns upside down or on its side

data.chText: 他猛然站起来，弄翻了椅子。
data.enText: He stood up quickly, overturning his chair.
to officially decide that a legal decision etc. is not correct, and to make it no longer valid

data.chText: 撤销决定 / 定罪 / 裁决
上诉法庭撤销了对他的判决。
data.enText: His sentence was overturned by the appeal court.

simple_means.memory_skill: over 翻转 + turn 转 → 翻转 → 颠覆

example: the biggest upset since David beat Goliath
he was badly bruised by the upset of his sled at a high speed
The Republicans were overruled when the House voted on the bill
He revoked the ban on smoking

tr: turn from an upright or normal position
cause to overturn from an upright or normal position
example: The cat knocked over the flower vase
the clumsy customer turned over the vase

value.def: If something overturns or if you overturn it, it turns upside down or on its side.

example.ex: The lorry veered out of control, overturned and smashed into a wall...
example.tran: 卡车突然失控，翻倒撞上了一堵墙。

example.ex: Alex jumped up so violently that he overturned his glass of sherry...
example.tran: 亚历克斯一下子暴跳起来，结果把他那杯雪利酒都打翻了。

example.ex: A dozen cartons of books had been overturned and strewn about the floor.
example.tran: 十几个装书的纸箱都被倒空，乱扔了一地。
千疮百孔的倾覆的小船

value.def: If someone in authority overturns a legal decision, they officially decide that that decision is incorrect or not valid.

example.ex: When the Russian parliament overturned his decision, he backed down...
example.tran: 俄罗斯议会推翻了他的决定，他只好作罢。

example.ex: His nine-month sentence was overturned by Appeal Court judge Lord Justice Watkins.
example.tran: 上诉法院法官沃特金斯撤销了对他作出的9个月徒刑的判决。

value.def: To overturn a government or system means to remove it or destroy it.

example.ex: He accused his opponents of wanting to overturn the government.
example.tran: 他指责反对派企图颠覆政府。

example.ex: ...a society where all the old values had been overturned.
example.tran: 摒弃了所有旧价值观的社会
